\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5185091 {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname State}}AL{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose}  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6165194\charrsid8142759 
I did for, after a while, but I didn't like it. I wanted to go home. I used to go home at night at first, only that was a two miles' walk from this place to the Wick Gate, and, er,
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15426346 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6165194\charrsid8142759 In the winter that must have been ..
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5185091 {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname State}}AL{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose}  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6165194\charrsid8142759 
In winter time so eventually I lived in. I lived there for a, quite a while, and er ..
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15426346 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6165194\charrsid8142759 How old were you when you first started there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5185091 {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname State}}AL{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose}  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6165194\charrsid8142759 
'Bout 12, um, 12 years old, just over, 'bout that, and, er, I lived then
, I got so tired and fed up with it. Oh, I did, and I was a very naughty girl, I got so tired and so homesick, I, well, things weren't very nice. They had another girl there, and she was a naughty, fast bit of stuff, you know, she }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3280237\charrsid8142759 wasn\rquote t}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6165194\charrsid8142759  very nice, and I g
ot so tired of her, and we kept getting so wrong with the, with the mistress, you know, she's gone now, and we used to, she said, there was a nurse in the house, 'cause she had another baby, this woman did, and, and she said she couldn't get us girls to d
o any work at all. We were waving out the window to the }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3280237\charrsid8142759 station porters}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6165194\charrsid8142759 
. It was ever so funny, but, um, she, ooh, we got, I got ever so wrong about it so, I thought to myself, well, I'm not stopping here, so, when the Saturday came, I, er, I remember Mrs. E
r ... the woman coming out, now, and she said to the other girl, she said, Ellen come and have your tea. {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname City}}Alice{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose}
, come if you want any. I said, thank you, I don't want any. She never took no notice of it; soon as they were gone, you know, I put my hat and coat on, and I was off home (..) never went back no more.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15426346 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6165194\charrsid8142759 Had you got your money; did they pay you by the \'85?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5185091 AL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6165194\charrsid8142759 Oh, yes, I got the money; it wasn't very much, but I always remember going along the road and a trap passed me, that was a Scotchman, and
, er, he, I run behind his cart, run behind that for a while, and then I got down to Anges Green }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6775460\charrsid8142759 \{BLANK\}}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6165194\charrsid8142759  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6775460\charrsid8142759 M}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6165194\charrsid8142759 y husband and }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6775460\charrsid8142759 I }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6165194\charrsid8142759 
used to laugh about it; I got to Anges Green and I went and knocked on a door and asked the man if he would go through the }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3280237\charrsid8142759 Honeypot}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid6165194\charrsid8142759  Lane; it's a lonely old place. I was too scared to go through there, so he went through, half-way through we met my Dad.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15426346 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6165194\charrsid8142759 And then what happened?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5185091 {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname State}}AL{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose}  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6165194\charrsid8142759 
He say, where are you going, girl. I said, I'm going home, I said, I ain't a-going to stop there no lo
nger, and I can hear him now, he said, you can't leave places like that you know. I said, oh, well I have, I'm going home, and I'm (not?) going back there no more. I never went back no more. And so he went back home with me to the Wick Gate, and so the ma
n went home, so (..) I never went back any more. And then, after a while, a very short time, I went to live down at the Wick Farm with a Scotch family, and a lovely family.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15426346 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6165194\charrsid8142759 That was the same farm where your father was working?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5185091 {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname State}}AL{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose}  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6165194\charrsid8142759 Yes, lived there, 
and they had several children, they had four or five babies there. Anne was born when I first went there, that one who's been my friend all my life, and her died last October. Can't get over losing Anne, but, she was, you know, ever so good to us, and, er
, used to, every week she used to take us out for a ride somewhere, and take us down to (..)
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15426346 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6165194\charrsid8142759 What did you go riding in? What sort of a vehicle?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5185091 {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname State}}AL{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose}  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6165194\charrsid8142759 Car.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15426346 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6165194\charrsid8142759 In a car? Oh, I see, you're talking about now.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5185091 {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname State}}AL{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose}  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6165194\charrsid8142759 Now. When I lived at the Wick ..

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15426346 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6165194\charrsid8142759 She was born while you were there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5185091 {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname State}}AL{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose}  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6165194\charrsid8142759 
Yes, while I was there. She was born in October. When I lived at the Wick they hadn't got a car, pony and trap.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15426346 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6165194\charrsid8142759 Yes, I was rather surprised when you said a car.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5185091 {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname State}}AL{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose}  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6165194\charrsid8142759 
I was running too far ahead, but I used to go, er, on the day when Mr. (..) Leamon, that was the Scotchman, to pay his rent. We children used to all pack in this trap, and go down to {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}Clacton{\*\xmlclose}
, and he used to pay his rent down there somewhere. I had a very happy life there. There was a lot of work, you know, four or five young children; I was the only one there, maid, like, but that was a happy home. Ooh, that was,
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15426346 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6165194\charrsid8142759 What sort of hours did you have to work there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5185091 {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname State}}AL{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose}  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6165194\charrsid8142759 
Well, my dear, it wasn't so long there as it was on the green }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6775460\charrsid8142759 \{BLANK\} }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6165194\charrsid8142759 on that fi
rst place I went. We (never?) used to go to bed till 10, {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname time}{\xmlattr\xmlattrns0{\xmlattrname Hour}{\xmlattrvalue 11}}{\xmlattr\xmlattrns0{\xmlattrname Minute}{\xmlattrvalue 0}}}11 o'clock{\*\xmlclose} at night. Up 
{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname time}{\xmlattr\xmlattrns0{\xmlattrname Hour}{\xmlattrvalue 18}}{\xmlattr\xmlattrns0{\xmlattrname Minute}{\xmlattrvalue 0}}}6 o'clock{\*\xmlclose} in the morning.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15426346 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6165194\charrsid8142759 That was on the green, you mean?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5185091 {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname State}}AL{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose}  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6165194\charrsid8142759 
Yes, at the, on the green, just by the station. That was very hard, but, er, I left it, and I, I went to the Scotch people ..
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15426346 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6165194\charrsid8142759 And you didn't regret it, I expect.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5185091 {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname State}}AL{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose}  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6165194\charrsid8142759 
Well, I had a lovely time. I lived there till I married. They didn't like me leaving, then and I know Mr. -,}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6775460\charrsid8142759  there was a somebody I, I got i}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid6165194\charrsid8142759 ll when I was there I got a bit run down or something. I remember Mr. (..) Leamont telling the, telling this man, he said, she's been a second mother to my children.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15426346 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6165194\charrsid8142759 So how many years did you stay there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5185091 {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname State}}AL{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose}  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6165194\charrsid8142759 
Six. I got married, you see, and they didn't like it. I was married when I was 20. They didn't like me leaving. They wanted me to stop on. I didn't want to do it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15426346 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6165194\charrsid8142759 Weren't they pleased that you were getting married?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5185091 {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname State}}AL{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose}  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6165194\charrsid8142759 
Well, they liked my husband, and all, I gone and lived up Angins Green, but, er, they were sorry to lose me, but their 
girls at, they always used to come and see me, and they used to go to school at Great Bentley, always used to call in there every night, but, um, there's nice family of them.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15426346 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6165194\charrsid8142759 Can you tell me a little bit more about the work there, because domestic service has almost vanished now?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5185091 {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname State}}AL{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose}  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6165194\charrsid8142759 
.. ordinary work, you know, get up in the morning, get the fire, and then get the breakfast for the family. Then wash the floors, and do the bedrooms, and all that kind of work, you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15426346 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6165194\charrsid8142759 Did the lady of the house work with you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5185091 AL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6165194\charrsid8142759 
Oh, she used to help me, oh, yes, she was a Scotch lady, and, er, but, of course, some of the time I got ill, and then they took me down to Scotland }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3280237\charrsid8142759 \{BLANK\} }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid6165194\charrsid8142759 holiday with the Scotch people, and they were lovely down there, mm, they were, ever such a nice family, but they're all, Mrs. (..) Leamont's gone, Mr. (..) Leamont }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid3280237\charrsid8142759 \{BLANK\} }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6165194\charrsid8142759 and now my Anne. It was awful losing her, that was. Terrible losing her.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15426346 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6165194\charrsid8142759 When you were there, did you have to cook at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5185091 {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname State}}AL{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose}  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6165194\charrsid8142759 Yes. I used to cook (..) I 
remember one day I made a cake, and some of the people come in for tea, and I (..) know the gentleman, my boss, he said, look that's the cake my girl's baked. Oh, I remember all them things.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15426346 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6165194\charrsid8142759 It's nice to hear these stories, because it's a life that's, you know, these things, working like that ..
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5185091 {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname State}}AL{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose}  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6165194\charrsid8142759 
And of course we used to have porridge and stuff, you know, porridge, and plenty of food, plenty of food there, and I can't say I did at that first job. Oh, goodness me. Oh, I remember that night when I,
 dark it was getting, and I come home, and I known that when I got back to the Wick Gate, my granddad, father was alone, was an old man, tall and that, and granny too. He said, never mind, never mind, girl, he say, if your mother and father can't keep you
, I will. Yes, (..) granddad said.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5185091 {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname State}}AL{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose}  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6165194\charrsid8142759 
Yes, because in those days it was very hard to keep girls .. It was hard work for me in that place up on the green. That was sort of a butcher's place. We used to make them pork cheese and stuff {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname time}
{\xmlattr\xmlattrns0{\xmlattrname Hour}{\xmlattrvalue 10}}{\xmlattr\xmlattrns0{\xmlattrname Minute}{\xmlattrvalue 0}}}10 o'clock{\*\xmlclose} at night. Oh, it was awful hard.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15426346 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6165194\charrsid8142759 Yes, and you were very young, weren't you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5185091 {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname State}}AL{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose}  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6165194\charrsid8142759 
I was young to go there, to that hard place.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15426346 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6165194\charrsid8142759 How did you find that job?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5185091 AL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6165194\charrsid8142759 Well, you see, I been a child, going to school, and my mother used to go there to work, used to 
walk from the Wick Gate up there to wash for a shilling a day. Isn't it awful when you think about it. Then they grumble now.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15426346 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6165194\charrsid8142759 And when she'd wait up there, did she hear they needed somebody?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5185091 AL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6165194\charrsid8142759 I expect (..) you know, Mrs., the woman was, the lady
 of the house, she really was, I was, very fond of me, but, er, our girl really, spoilt, but still I think I was best to come away. I didn't regret it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15426346 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6165194\charrsid8142759 And when you went away and got your next job, did you get better money?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5185091 AL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6165194\charrsid8142759 Well, I think I had six pounds for six months.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15426346 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6165194\charrsid8142759 In your next job, or the one on the green?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5185091 AL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6165194\charrsid8142759 
Five shillings, five shillings a week, at the next job, but the first job, I think that was a shilling. One shilling, or two shilling; it wan't much. I think I had got two shillings or half-a-crown, that's all.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15426346 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6165194\charrsid8142759 And what did you do with the money?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5185091 AL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6165194\charrsid8142759 I don't know, used to buy clothes and things.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15426346 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6165194\charrsid8142759 Were you expected to give any to your parents?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5185091 AL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6165194\charrsid8142759 I think I, yes, I think I did; I think I used to give them must didn't have a lot you know,
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15426346 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6165194\charrsid8142759 And did your sisters also have domestic work?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5185091 AL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6165194\charrsid8142759 Oh, yes, my sister now what died at {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}Clacton{\*\xmlclose}
, she used to go in, she was in service, you know, and, er, my sister down there, De Vere Estate, Mrs. Manning, she goes out to all different places now.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15426346 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6165194\charrsid8142759 She did when she was a girl too?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5185091 AL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6165194\charrsid8142759 Oh, she, she (..) used to go out to work as a matter of fact, when I left the Scotch family, she took it on. She went there.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15426346 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6165194\charrsid8142759 They must have been pleased about that, to have one of the family, weren't they?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5185091 AL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6165194\charrsid8142759 Mm. Oh, yes, they were very good to her. They were like \'85. Oh, they were ever so good to me.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15426346 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6165194\charrsid8142759 When you were a child, could you tell me something about the way, food your mother used to cook; you told me she used to bake her bread ..

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5185091 AL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6165194\charrsid8142759 Used to bake her bread (..) and that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15426346 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6165194\charrsid8142759 What sort of breakfast did you used to have in those days?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5185091 AL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6165194\charrsid8142759 Bread and butter, and sometimes, I think she used to make porridge, you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15426346 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6165194\charrsid8142759 Did you have anything on your porridge?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5185091 AL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6165194\charrsid8142759 Sugar, I suppose.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15426346 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6165194\charrsid8142759 Did you ever have milk to drink?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5185091 AL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6165194\charrsid8142759 
Well, we didn't have a lot, but we used, I had plenty when I got to the Scotch people, but, we used to have, you know, used to keep us going with what we could get, like, (..) a big lot of food, but still kept us going.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15426346 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6165194\charrsid8142759 Did you have dinner in the middle of the day then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5185091 AL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6165194\charrsid8142759 Yes, er, well, of course, I used to be at school; I'd take my food with me to the school, and my dad used to come in to dinner 
{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname time}{\xmlattr\xmlattrns0{\xmlattrname Hour}{\xmlattrvalue 15}}{\xmlattr\xmlattrns0{\xmlattrname Minute}{\xmlattrvalue 0}}}three o'clock{\*\xmlclose}. Sometimes mother used to save u
s some for night, and, my granny used to save us some hot stuff, vegetables and puddings, and things they used to make in a good old suet puddings and things like that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15426346 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6165194\charrsid8142759 When you had suet puddings, did they start the meal with them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5185091 AL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6165194\charrsid8142759 Well, if they had any gravy or anything, but of co}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8847745\charrsid8142759 
urse (..) you didn't always have }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6165194\charrsid8142759 that did you}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8847745\charrsid8142759 ?,}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6165194\charrsid8142759 
 they used to have sugar or sometimes some syrup, I think; when I went to school sometimes my mother used to pack up some bread, and I, she used to put a cup in the bag and
 give me a ha'penny, ha'penny; used to go to the shop and get a ha' p' orth of treacle. That was the days. Whatever would the kids think now I don't know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15426346 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6165194\charrsid8142759 Did you have anything to drink?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5185091 AL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6165194\charrsid8142759 Water. Used to go round the houses for water. They got so 
tired of us going round for a drink that they, they grumbled about it. The water at the school wasn't very good, no, not very pure, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15426346 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6165194\charrsid8142759 Then, when you came back home in the evening, did you have some more food then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5185091 AL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6165194\charrsid8142759 Well, you see, I say, mother used to sometimes save us some.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15426346 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6165194\charrsid8142759 Of course you did that was when you had something hot?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5185091 AL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6165194\charrsid8142759 Yes, yes, at night.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15426346 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6165194\charrsid8142759 How often did you have meat in those days?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5185091 AL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6165194\charrsid8142759 We didn't used to have a lot, but of course meat was cheaper then. I know when we u
sed to have some, Christmas Day, and, er, farmer used to give him a joint of beef for Christmas. Fifteen shillings a week, and that weren't a lot.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15426346 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6165194\charrsid8142759 Did he have to pay rent, or was it a cottage that belonged to the farmer?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5185091 AL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6165194\charrsid8142759 Well, I don't think my d
ad had to pay rent. No, I don't think he did. I think they were sort of, he was head horse-man; I think he got that sort of free, the rent. (..) little man he was.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15426346 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6165194\charrsid8142759 Do you remember what your mother and father did in their spare time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5185091 AL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6165194\charrsid8142759 My dad couldn't read or write.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15426346 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6165194\charrsid8142759 Had he been to school at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5185091 AL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6165194\charrsid8142759 He went to school (..) when he was in {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname City}}Suffolk{\*\xmlclose}
{\*\xmlclose}. But he said all the time he was at school he was put on a dunce's stool.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15426346 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6165194\charrsid8142759 So, did you ever have a newspaper in the house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5185091 AL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6165194\charrsid8142759 Well, (..) I used to buy the \{illegible\}, {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname City}}Suffolk
{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose} chronicle and Mercury? You know. I don't know if that's in print now. No, don't think so.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15426346 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6165194\charrsid8142759 Did your mother read?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5185091 AL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6165194\charrsid8142759 Mother could read. Yes. But father couldn't.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15426346 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6165194\charrsid8142759 Did she read to him?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5185091 AL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6165194\charrsid8142759 Well, yes, and we children used to read to him.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15426346 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6165194\charrsid8142759 Did you get report cards when you were at the school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5185091 AL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6165194\charrsid8142759 Oh, no, we never had much of that. That come on after we left.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15426346 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6165194\charrsid8142759 Were your mother and father interested in the school, what you were doing at school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5185091 AL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6165194\charrsid8142759 Yes, I
 suppose they were. They'd tell us we were naughty children, and all of that, you know. We used to get up to all sorts of capers. My little brother died when he was a year and five months old. (..) so I didn't have a brother.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15426346 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6165194\charrsid8142759 Do you remember what sort of games you used to play when you were a girl at school? Did you play a lot with other children?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5185091 AL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6165194\charrsid8142759 
Used to play marbles, skipping, we used to get grumbled if we'd been skipping, skipping the shoes off. Used to get measured for shoes, shoe-maker used 
to come from Little Bentley and measure us and we were ever so pleased we got new shoes, but I don't think our parents were 'cause they had to pay for them. When I think about all what they had and what they had to do, it was very hard, was a very hard li
fe for them.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15426346 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6165194\charrsid8142759 Most people, I think, in those days only had one pair of shoes at a time. Were you like that? Or did you have Sunday shoes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5185091 AL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6165194\charrsid8142759 Now, I believe, we did have some Sunday ones, but didn't have a lot (..) he used to have long frocks on right down to your toes.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15426346 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6165194\charrsid8142759 Every day?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5185091 AL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6165194\charrsid8142759 
Yes, long dresses, you know, not these here short ones. Oh, dear. I remember other children used to have gaiters, and I can remember once my mother made me a pair. I can see them gaiters now, and she made us go to
 school in them; we, I didn't like it, because they were only home made and (..) buttoned round.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15426346 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6165194\charrsid8142759 Did she sew a lot?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5185091 AL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6165194\charrsid8142759 Mother could sew, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15426346 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6165194\charrsid8142759 Did she make clothes for all of you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5185091 AL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6165194\charrsid8142759 She would make some you see, and she was out at service.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15426346 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6165194\charrsid8142759 Was she out in service before she married?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5185091 AL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6165194\charrsid8142759 Before she married. She was cook down at (..) St. Osyth some where
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15426346 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6165194\charrsid8142759 And after she married did she start working quite soon again?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5185091 AL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6165194\charrsid8142759 Well, after she got married she used to, er, go out to work on 
the farms, picking up stones in the fields and things like that to get some money.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15426346 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6165194\charrsid8142759 Did she do that after the children were born?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5185091 AL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6165194\charrsid8142759 Yes, 'cause I remember we went with her (..) when me got sort of manners and she used to go gleaning, and get corn, 
you know, and then they used to (..) have it ground and made into flour.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15426346 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6165194\charrsid8142759 Did you go gleaning with her?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5185091 AL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6165194\charrsid8142759 Yes, but we didn't like it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15426346 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6165194\charrsid8142759 No, why not?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5185091 AL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6165194\charrsid8142759 Well, we didn't want to be working, did we?. We didn't understand did we?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15426346 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6165194\charrsid8142759 Did a lot of children go?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5185091 AL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6165194\charrsid8142759 
Well, I suppose they did. Of course, we lived out of the village (..) hiring down the Wick Gate. Oh, they were a bit hard times, but still, we got over them. Then when I was 20 I got married and lived at Angiens Green.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15426346 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6165194\charrsid8142759 Do you mind me asking you where you met your husband, or would you rather ..?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5185091 AL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6165194\charrsid8142759 Well, I can tell you if you like. I met him across at the chapel over here, the Methodist church.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15426346 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6165194\charrsid8142759 Were your parents Methodists?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5185091 AL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6165194\charrsid8142759 His parents, yes, we were all Methodists, a
nd his parents were, and I met him at there, you see, and there was some more boys after me at the time, but, I know, er, I went, I went from the Wick Gate, and my aunt and uncle lived there. I used to go to the chapel with them. Well, then when we came o
u
t at night, you see, my husband used to be there, young boy, like, well, he was getting on, and when we came out he used to come with me to a certain distance. My aunt and uncle used to keep sort of near, so then when I used to bid him goodnight we all we
nt up together. That went on for some time. My parents didn't know.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15426346 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6165194\charrsid8142759 You didn't tell them about it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5185091 AL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6165194\charrsid8142759 No. No. I didn't tell them, but they found out. They found out. My aunt has gone and my uncle's gone. Lots of people gone.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15426346 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6165194\charrsid8142759 Did you soon prefer him to the other boys who were after you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5185091 AL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6165194\charrsid8142759 Oh, yes. I never (..) the others; didn't want those they used to, I got some when I was in {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}
{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname country-region}}Scotland{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose}, boys, Scotch boys after me. He, he was a good boy. We married 60 years.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15426346 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6165194\charrsid8142759 Did you have a long engagement?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5185091 AL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6165194\charrsid8142759 'Bout three years or so.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15426346 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6165194\charrsid8142759 And were you working at the farm during that time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5185091 AL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6165194\charrsid8142759 Yes. Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15426346 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6165194\charrsid8142759 Was he allowed to come and see you there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5185091 AL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6165194\charrsid8142759 Yes, he come down there.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15426346 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6165194\charrsid8142759 Could you entertain him?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5185091 AL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6165194\charrsid8142759 Oh, yes. The Scotch people, you can do as you like. \{illegible\} they were easy going. They were ever so good to us.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15426346 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6165194\charrsid8142759 Did you get married in the Methodist chapel?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5185091 AL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6165194\charrsid8142759 Yes. I was christened there, and I got married there.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15426346 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6165194\charrsid8142759 Then, when you got married, did you go and live back in Angers Green?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5185091 AL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6165194\charrsid8142759 Yes. (..) Angers Green, lived there for six years, and then I went down on the (..) The The houses are all down now. He worked on the farm.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15426346 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6165194\charrsid8142759 Which farm was that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5185091 AL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6165194\charrsid8142759 Same farm.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15426346 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6165194\charrsid8142759 As your father?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5185091 AL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6165194\charrsid8142759 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15426346 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6165194\charrsid8142759 Was he also a horse-man?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5185091 AL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6165194\charrsid8142759 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15426346 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6165194\charrsid8142759 Can you remember what money he was earning when you first got married?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5185091 AL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6165194\charrsid8142759 Well, about, er, fifteen shillings a week. I think that dropped to fourteen, and now I tell you what ..
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15426346 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6165194\charrsid8142759 When (?) did it drop?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5185091 AL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6165194\charrsid8142759 Don't know. I t
ell you what I had to keep house on, ten shillings a week. That was a bit of a job. And we used to go and, you heard what that man said, we used to get the harvest bonus, then we used to go to {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}Colchester{\*\xmlclose}
 and get some clothes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15426346 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6165194\charrsid8142759 How did you get into {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}Colchester{\*\xmlclose}?
