ed a shield for the Sunday School, did that, and he talked to them a bit, and then, and the service was nearly over and I thought to myself, I couldn't sing a note. I wasn't a bit interested, and that's the truth, and I thought to myself, well, I'm not co
ming over here any more today, because there was afternoon and evening. I know what I shall do. (..) \{BLANK\}
 So after the service was over I went up to the front there where the minister was, so I said, er, 'cause he knows my people well, he goes to Butlin'
