{\*\xmlclose}. People go out, they don't make no fuss about that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15426346 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6165194\charrsid8142759 And were they fussy about when you came in at night?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5185091 AL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6165194\charrsid8142759 No. 'Cause I slept there for a while, and then I went home to sleep at Granny's, for company for her
, and that was, that, the lady of the house said, we can't ever find that bedroom of yours, they were wonders to find all the bedrooms, but the one I had had got no fireplace, and I said I was too cold for me in the winter, so I went to granny's and slept
 there, and then, course when the better weather come they wanted me to stop, and I didn't want to. I wanted to go home, and I got the (..) day and/went home.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15426346 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6165194\charrsid8142759 Did you get on easily with your father and mother?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5185091 AL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6165194\charrsid8142759 Oh, yes, that was all right. Oh, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15426346 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6165194\charrsid8142759 Were they strict parents?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5185091 AL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6165194\charrsid8142759 Well, they might have been, but they, they weren't too bad. Poor old dad he was a nice old chap.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15426346 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6165194\charrsid8142759 Yes, he sounds very sweet what you said about when you left the job and how he spoke to you. I think some people say th}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2174603\charrsid8142759 at parents were stricter then}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6165194\charrsid8142759 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5185091 AL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6165194\charrsid8142759 Can you see there? Oh, yes, you can see the, look, can't you?;
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15426346 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6165194\charrsid8142759 Yes, that's why I said, was it 1935?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5185091 AL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6165194\charrsid8142759 It's when they were married, and then that was their golden wedding.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15426346 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6165194\charrsid8142759 When you say she was a very determined woman ..?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5185091 AL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6165194\charrsid8142759 Well, you know, she knew what she wanted (..) she wouldn't \{illegible\}
 down to any body but they were very good parents, they never, they weren't you know ..
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15426346 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6165194\charrsid8142759 Some people were telling me, that in those days children were brough
t up very much to call some people "Sir" and not other people. Could you tell me something about that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5185091 AL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6165194\charrsid8142759 
Well, I don't think I did much of that, but my granny used to have to, and I seen her, 'cause there used to be somebody come up there on horseback from (..) \{ILLEGIBLE\}
 I can't remember his name now, and she, she used to curtsey to him, and I, I never do that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15426346 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6165194\charrsid8142759 No, you weren't brought up to do that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5185091 AL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6165194\charrsid8142759 No, I never done that. We had to be polite and all like that to people, but we never done that.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15426346 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6165194\charrsid8142759 Were you brought up to think of people as being very different stations in life?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5185091 AL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6165194\charrsid8142759 
Well, you always knew that, didn't you? You just, you know, dear, dear, I remember sitting on a policeman's lap when I was a little girl, policeman come in to see my granny, he wan't coming after her for anything. I know he took me on his lap
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15426346 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6165194\charrsid8142759 You weren't brought up to be frightened of the police?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5185091 AL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6165194\charrsid8142759 No. Didn't like them much. I didn't like them.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15426346 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6165194\charrsid8142759 Did your mother ever say she would call a policeman if you were naughty?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5185091 AL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6165194\charrsid8142759 Oh, yes (..) I'll call a policeman into you
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15426346 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6165194\charrsid8142759 Was she fussy about how you behaved at table?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5185091 AL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6165194\charrsid8142759 Oh, yes, we had to behave. Oh, we were brought up to behave. We had to be polite to people and say "please" and "thank you" and al
l like that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15426346 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6165194\charrsid8142759 When you used to have meals, did you all sit down together?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5185091 AL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6165194\charrsid8142759 Yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15426346 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6165194\charrsid8142759 And did you have to, did somebody say grace?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5185091 AL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6165194\charrsid8142759 Oh, yes, they used to, so did my husband's father ..
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15426346 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6165194\charrsid8142759 When you were married, did you say grace or your husband?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5185091 AL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6165194\charrsid8142759 Yes, my husband, and his father always did. He was brought up with it, you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15426346 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6165194\charrsid8142759 What meals did they say it at?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5185091 AL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6165194\charrsid8142759 His father used to say it at every one.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15426346 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6165194\charrsid8142759 And your father, did he say it, or was it your mother who said it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5185091 AL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6165194\charrsid8142759 Mother or father, you know, we girls, we children had to say it. Yes, we had to say it. We used to have to say it, you know, grace.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15426346 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6165194\charrsid8142759 And did you say it at all meals?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5185091 AL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6165194\charrsid8142759 I bet we had to. Brought up a bit strict like that you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15426346 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6165194\charrsid8142759 If your mother cooked something and you didn't like it, did she want you to eat something of it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5185091 AL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6165194\charrsid8142759 Well, you'll have to eat it or leave it. That's it. Couldn't waste things.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15426346 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6165194\charrsid8142759 You mean if you had something on your plate, did you have to finish it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5185091 AL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6165194\charrsid8142759 We had to finish it. You can take, take it or leave it, you know, you know, you, we didn't have any more.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15426346 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6165194\charrsid8142759 And could you get down when you had finished?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5185091 AL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6165194\charrsid8142759 When the time come.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15426346 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6165194\charrsid8142759 Did you have to wait till the others had finished?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5185091 AL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6165194\charrsid8142759 Yes. Yes. We weren't allowed to run about and that before.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15426346 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6165194\charrsid8142759 A lot of those things have changed now, that's why I am interested in asking you, children do run round ..
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5185091 AL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6165194\charrsid8142759 They run around (..) behave anyhow don't they?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15426346 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6165194\charrsid8142759 Were you allowed to talk at meals?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5185091 AL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6165194\charrsid8142759 No. You mustn't talk at meals. Mustn't talk. You've got to be quiet and behave yourself, that's what I used to say.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15426346 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6165194\charrsid8142759 Did you have any children?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5185091 AL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6165194\charrsid8142759 No. Never had any. I couldn't have any. My husband was very fond of children. We had several (..) others 
on you know my own family, but I've never had any, I couldn't have any for some reason, which could not be helped.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15426346 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6165194\charrsid8142759 Did you keep any animals or pets?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5185091 AL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6165194\charrsid8142759 Dogs, we had dogs all our life. We used to have some chickens, hens and chickens.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15426346 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6165194\charrsid8142759 Did you ever keep a pig?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5185091 AL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6165194\charrsid8142759 No. That's difficult. Yes, that was difficult. His father did on the (..) \{BLANK\}
 his father used to keep pigs, and I think my granny did at the Wick Gate, and she used to have bees and get a lot of honey.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15426346 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6165194\charrsid8142759 Did you ever keep bees, or help her?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5185091 AL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6165194\charrsid8142759 No fear. I'm too frightened to keep bees; I know when they used to clear the honey out I used to be ever so afraid of the bees.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15426346 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6165194\charrsid8142759 When you were a little girl did your mother and father ever punish you if you were naughty?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5185091 AL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6165194\charrsid8142759 (..) }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5597594\charrsid8142759 \{BLANK\} }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid6165194\charrsid8142759 box the ears (..)
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15426346 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6165194\charrsid8142759 Did you ever get a hiding?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5185091 AL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6165194\charrsid8142759 No. Not bad. No. Never.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15426346 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6165194\charrsid8142759 Did you ever get sent to bed without supper?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5185091 AL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6165194\charrsid8142759 Yes, I did. Now, I did. I remember, you know, we didn't have any money to spend; there wasn't any, and this mor
ning especially I did want a penny to get something with. Well, mother had got a whole pile of money, coppers, piled up on the mantelpiece, and I thought, well, she won't miss that. Poor old thing, I can see now, she'd got that counted out for the shopman
,
 or something. Well, I took a penny, and I, er, course went to school and I had this, what I wanted with this penny. When I got home my mother was there, and my aunt, she said, first thing, did you take a penny off that mantelpiece? Course I said I didn't
. She said, you must have done, she said, because there was a penny missing, and, course, I had to confess I did, and I got sent to bed without my tea, for taking a penny. They used to talk about it afterwards; you remember stealing that penny?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15426346 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6165194\charrsid8142759 The fact that you remember it so well makes you think perhaps you didn't do a lot of naughty things when you were a little girl, did you?

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5185091 AL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6165194\charrsid8142759 No. Like others, you know, we used to get up to mischief, my sister and I sometimes playing about, but, never done too bad.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15426346 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6165194\charrsid8142759 Did you have regular set jobs, you and your sister, that you had to do?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5185091 AL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6165194\charrsid8142759 
Well, I can't say we did. Just helped mother a bit, and I do remember when I used to go out to a friend of ours, on a Saturday morning. We used to get threepence for t
he, I used to get threepence for the day, doing little odd jobs. I, I didn't keep on with that long.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15426346 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6165194\charrsid8142759 What sort of odd jobs were those?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5185091 AL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6165194\charrsid8142759 Oh, just housework, and washing-up, and sweeping up; like my sister when she come here the other day. She said
, I've come to sweep your carpets. I said, well, I took a long broom, I said, and, and swept them. She said, that's not the way to do carpets. You want to get down on your knees, and do them. I said, you wouldn't get down on your knees if you'd got such a
 sore knee as I have. I had a tumble you see, see, I've got it all bandaged up now, and I can't kneel on that knee.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15426346 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6165194\charrsid8142759 When you were first looking after your own home, did you do certain things on certain days?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5185091 AL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6165194\charrsid8142759 Oh, yes, I used to do the bedrooms two or three times a week. My husband used to say, you don't want to do that, but ..
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15426346 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6165194\charrsid8142759 You mean he thought you did too much housework?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5185091 AL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6165194\charrsid8142759 Yes. Course that was unfortunate I got ill; had a nasty breakdown, and I couldn't do anything for quite a while.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15426346 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6165194\charrsid8142759 How did you manage, then? When you couldn't do the housework?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5185091 AL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6165194\charrsid8142759 
(..) Well my husband was very good, and I managed somehow. Oh, yes, mother used to come up, and, and I, you know, my sister used to come and ..
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15426346 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6165194\charrsid8142759 Did any neighbours, or any people who weren't related to you help you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5185091 AL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6165194\charrsid8142759 
No, I can't speak too well of the neighbours that I had, I'm sorry. They were too interfering. They used to interfere with me so much, if I went out (..) "She's out again" I couldn't do as I liked, and I really thi
nk that was some of it what made me ill. They were always finding fault with me, that's the truth. They've all gone now, so they won't harm.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15426346 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6165194\charrsid8142759 You mean they didn't have enough to occupy their own minds; they were watching you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5185091 AL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6165194\charrsid8142759 Watching me about.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15426346 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6165194\charrsid8142759 Were they older people, or were they your own age?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5185091 AL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6165194\charrsid8142759 Well, there was one old lady, and her daughter, but, you know.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15426346 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6165194\charrsid8142759 Could you describe what your kitchen was like, and your living room, when you were first married?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5185091 AL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6165194\charrsid8142759 Well, just a little ba
ck room with a, just a fireplace, and er nothing on it, just a coal fire, and used to have to heat the water on the fire in a kettle.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15426346 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6165194\charrsid8142759 You said you used to try to bake bread .. ?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5185091 AL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6165194\charrsid8142759 (..) That was at mothers at the Wick Gate, and the houses are all down, which I was going to show you today if we have went out.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15426346 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6165194\charrsid8142759 So when you baked, you'd go and bake at your mother's house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5185091 AL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6165194\charrsid8142759 I used to bake at my, we used to bake at mother's didn't we, Flo?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15426346 K2  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6165194\charrsid8142759 (Flo) Yes.</subject2>
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15426346 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6165194\charrsid8142759 Did you have any oven at all at your own place?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5185091 AL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6165194\charrsid8142759 Never had an oven, did I, didn't have any oven no cooking ... not at Anges Green.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15426346 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6165194\charrsid8142759 You told me you went to Southend. Did you have any other day outings like that when you were married
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5185091 AL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6165194\charrsid8142759 Every six months we used to go up to Colchester, no, no, har-, after the harvest, we used to go up and spend the bonus of the harvest (..)

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15426346 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6165194\charrsid8142759 You didn't have any chapel outings?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5185091 AL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6165194\charrsid8142759 No. (..) Nothing of that again
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15426346 K2  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6165194\charrsid8142759 (Another voice) Not when you were married.</subject2>
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15426346 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6165194\charrsid8142759 I was also going to ask you how you managed with the washing in those days.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5185091 AL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6165194\charrsid8142759 Well, I'll tell you. I had a boiler, and used to ..
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15426346 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6165194\charrsid8142759 Was that in your ..?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5185091 AL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6165194\charrsid8142759 No, they used to put that on in the wash house next door, on a coal fire, and put the boiler on.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15426346 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6165194\charrsid8142759 And then what did you do?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5185091 AL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6165194\charrsid8142759 Washed the linen, and boiled it, and then you used to have to hand it out.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15426346 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6165194\charrsid8142759 If it didn't get dry what did you do?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5185091 AL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6165194\charrsid8142759 Well, just have to wait till it did. Leave it till it did get dry.
\par  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15426346 K2  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6165194\charrsid8142759 Tell you one thing
 what we used to do was pick up these cones, you know, they used to be fir cones; go out and put them on the fire and they used to help boil the water (..) my mother's place, I didn't remember it at my sister's (Mrs. Lambert) (..)}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15426346 K2  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6165194\charrsid8142759 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15426346 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6165194\charrsid8142759 Did you have any different food on Sundays from what you might have on another day?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5185091 AL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6165194\charrsid8142759 
Well, on Sunday, I generally used to, I used to get a little joint on Saturday, and that generally come to about 1s. 4d., and now that'd cost about six or seven shillings, and then
 I tell you what I generally used to make, I didn't used to cook on Sundays. I used to cook this on the Saturday, and I generally used to make some pastry, a tart or something, you know, with some sort of fruit (..) and have a milk pudding with it. That's
 what we had for Sunday dinner, but we generally used to walk from Angers Green, my husband and I after the Methodist church, walk, no (..) bike.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15426346 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6165194\charrsid8142759 Did you ever have a bike?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5185091 AL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6165194\charrsid8142759 Yes. I did have a bicycle. After some years I had a bicycle.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15426346 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6165194\charrsid8142759 When you had your bicycle, did you bicycle up to the chapel?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5185091 AL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6165194\charrsid8142759 Yes, I think we did, didn't we?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15426346 K2  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6165194\charrsid8142759 Sometimes.</subject2>
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5185091 AL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6165194\charrsid8142759 Sometimes, yes we did. The road used to be full of people \{BLANK\} that road down by the station, people going to church and chapel,
 and now the}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3280237\charrsid8142759 re\rquote s nobody s}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6165194\charrsid8142759 o. It's dreadful now really.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15426346 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6165194\charrsid8142759 Did your husband help at all in the housework?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5185091 AL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6165194\charrsid8142759 He was a clever boy in the house. I had a ..
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5185091 AL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6165194\charrsid8142759 Oh, yes, my husband was ever so good, and once, once I was ill for two or three months, I had
 a nervous breakdown, and he used to, matter of fact he was, he'd had a long illness, but he was convalescent and the doctors just put him off like that, and he used to do lot of little jobs (..) when stopped the time, that made us. Some years ago when I 
lived down the Green here, and I remember one day he made ever, ever such a nice ginger pudding (..) He could do cooking couldn't he? like in the house, he could do house work too very well, but, er, he used to say, well, I was, well, I did too much.

\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15426346 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6165194\charrsid8142759 When you had meals when you were married which room did you eat them in? Could you eat in the kitchen; was there room enough?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5185091 AL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6165194\charrsid8142759 Oh, yes. In the kitchen at Angers Green. When we went to the (..) \{ILLEGIBLE\} yes we could.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15426346 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6165194\charrsid8142759 Did you still have the midday meal at 3 o'clock?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5185091 AL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6165194\charrsid8142759 
At 3 o'clock in the afternoon. My husband used to have 3 o'clock dinner, but often he didn't come home till night and have his dinner at night.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15426346 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6165194\charrsid8142759 Would he take something with him?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5185091 AL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6165194\charrsid8142759 Take his lunch and that with him, and then we used to have our, I used to cook at night. That's right.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15426346 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6165194\charrsid8142759 And did you have the same food as him?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5185091 AL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6165194\charrsid8142759 Oh, yes, of course I did.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15426346 K2  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6165194\charrsid8142759 (Voice in background difficult to make out on this side; also people talking at once.)</subject2>
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15426346 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6165194\charrsid8142759 They call it \{illegible\} at 11 o'clock.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15426346 K2  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6165194\charrsid8142759 Flo. And in the summer lane at harvest they used to call it because-12 o'clock \{ILLEGIBLE\}. That's night \{ILLEGIBLE\}</subject2>
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15426346 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6165194\charrsid8142759 That's Essex I suppose?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5185091 AL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6165194\charrsid8142759 That's Essex.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15426346 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6165194\charrsid8142759 How often did you have meat when you were married?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5185091 AL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6165194\charrsid8142759 (..) Oh, me used to have a little you know, but that was ..
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15426346 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6165194\charrsid8142759 How many times a week?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5185091 AL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6165194\charrsid8142759 Generally had some every day, something, some sort you know, but, 'course it was ...
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15426346 K2  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6165194\charrsid8142759 (Voice) Cheaper, wasn't it.</subject2>
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15426346 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6165194\charrsid8142759 When you were a little girl did you play with other children besides your sisters?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5185091 AL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6165194\charrsid8142759 
Do you know, I went to school when I was eight or nine or ten, didn't I, Flo. I left school when I was twelve so. I didn't have much time to play, did I. Went to work, went out to work then when I was about 12 years old. Come up on the Green here, Flo.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15426346 K2  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6165194\charrsid8142759 (Flo). That's right. We had two miles and a half to walk to school every morning. No buses(..)</subject2>
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15426346 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6165194\charrsid8142759 How old did you say you were when you started school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5185091 AL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6165194\charrsid8142759 
(..) I was about 9 or 10, 8 or 9 or something I went to that little school on Angels Green first, I went there, I think I was about eight or something, or was I older than that
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15426346 K2  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6165194\charrsid8142759 (..) well you }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3280237\charrsid8142759 weren\rquote t}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid6165194\charrsid8142759  so old then 6 or 8 or 9?</subject2>
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5185091 AL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6165194\charrsid8142759 I didn't go till I was 6 (..)
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15426346 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6165194\charrsid8142759 When you say 6 or 8 you're talking about the school up here by the (..) green
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5185091 AL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6165194\charrsid8142759 (..) Yes, yes, that's right.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15426346 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6165194\charrsid8142759 Did you ever go up to the}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3280237\charrsid8142759  school up here that was the Bonn}{\rtlch\fcs1 
\af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6165194\charrsid8142759 el school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5185091 AL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6165194\charrsid8142759 Oh, yes, after I got, I come, used to come up here to the school \{BLANK\}
 to the hall here. I went to the hall first, then I went across to the Methodist school, Wesleyan, they used to call it. Well, after that they built this new school, and I went there for a very short period. Then I left when I was twelve years old.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15426346 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6165194\charrsid8142759 So that was four different places altogether.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5185091 AL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6165194\charrsid8142759 I had four schools, Angers Green, and three at Great Bentley.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15426346 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6165194\charrsid8142759 What kind of school was the Anges Green one? Who was it run by?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5185091 AL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6165194\charrsid8142759 Oh, (..) a governess a Miss Beavers or something. (..) She don't remember, \{illegible\}
 she won't remember. (..) it used to be packed with children, packed with children.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15426346 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6165194\charrsid8142759 How many rooms?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5185091 AL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6165194\charrsid8142759 There was just this one big room and a little gallery, and then there was outside places,
 you see, and we could go out to the lavatory if we wanted, they were only just pail lavatories.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15426346 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6165194\charrsid8142759 Do you know if your parents had to pay or not?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5185091 AL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6165194\charrsid8142759 No. I don't think they did. They did earlier, before that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15426346 K2  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6165194\charrsid8142759 Dad had to when he went to school.</subject2>
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5185091 AL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6165194\charrsid8142759 Dad didn't go to school.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15426346 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6165194\charrsid8142759 (..) Referring to Dad's education.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15426346 K2  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6165194\charrsid8142759 .. they never wanted you after you'd paid your twopence.</subject2>
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15426346 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6165194\charrsid8142759 Just wanted you for the money?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5185091 AL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6165194\charrsid8142759 But poor old Dad ..
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15426346 K2  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6165194\charrsid8142759 Could neither read nor write at 82.</subject2>
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5185091 AL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6165194\charrsid8142759 
(Mrs. Lambert) And he used to spend his time on the dunces. I told you so before (..) on the dunce's stool, on a high stool where they put the (..) naughty ...
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15426346 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6165194\charrsid8142759 Was it boys and girls at Anges Green?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5185091 AL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6165194\charrsid8142759 Yes, and, er, there was, used to be full, and I remember one day .. (Voice) (rather indistinct, and all talking together)
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15426346 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6165194\charrsid8142759 You were telling me about the school; I asked you if it was boys and girls.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5185091 AL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6165194\charrsid8142759 Yes, that was boys and girls, and we all used to sit sort of together, yo
u know, in forms, like, um, and I remember one incident one day, the teacher, there used to be one governess for all that lot, and, er, she had to go out of the room for a little while to see somebody, she just had had her lodgings next door and there was
 pandemonium (..) oh they were ahead something frightful.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15426346 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6165194\charrsid8142759 How many of them were there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5185091 AL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6165194\charrsid8142759 Oh, there was forty or fifty I should think, really, there must have been, in that bit of school,
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15426346 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6165194\charrsid8142759 And up to what age did they stay on there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5185091 AL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6165194\charrsid8142759 Well, 
I think I must have come up to Great Bentley when I was 9 or 10, or something, 'cause you see I left when I was only 12 years old. I think that was them.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15426346 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6165194\charrsid8142759 Did you ever have to wear school uniform at any of your schools?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5185091 AL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6165194\charrsid8142759 We had to wear what we could get. We had to wear what me could get.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15426346 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6165194\charrsid8142759 Do you remember anything you were taught at school, I mean, how they taught you in those days?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5185091 AL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6165194\charrsid8142759 (..) you know, teach us the alphabet and things like that, but I remember one incident, my sister and I, wer
e coming up to the school in the morning, and when we got halfway through this rather lonely road we saw some gypsy caravans. They used to stop there at night and we wouldn't go to school, we went back home again. Afraid. And another incidence, I remember
 
my sister, my sister's dead now, she died last October, um, we were going to school and it rained so fast that my granny, my mother wouldn't let us come, and we went in the afternoon or something, and when we, that cleared up a bit, we went later, and whe
n we went in the school the teacher says, here comes the babies stopping away for a drop of rain. (..) I used to remember all that.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15426346 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6165194\charrsid8142759 Did you like the teachers on the whole?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5185091 AL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6165194\charrsid8142759 Oh, they were very nice teachers, oh, yes, they were very nice.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15426346 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6165194\charrsid8142759 When you went to the little school at Angers Green with the governess, did you go home for your dinner then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5185091 AL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6165194\charrsid8142759 
I think we took some with us, and then went home in the afternoon, I think I don't think we went home to dinner, 'cause that's rather long way, you see to Wick Gate, that was a mile or so, lonely old roads.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15426346 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6165194\charrsid8142759 
When you were a child, can you tell me about, you said how there wasn't a bathroom, and there was only a well, what did your mother do about bathing you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5185091 AL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6165194\charrsid8142759 Bath in the kitchen and bathed in the kitchen.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15426346 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6165194\charrsid8142759 Did she do it at a regular time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5185091 AL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6165194\charrsid8142759 Oh, yes, I, it was always on Saturdays anyhow, you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15426346 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6165194\charrsid8142759 Must have been hard work.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5185091 AL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6165194\charrsid8142759 Was hard work, carting water in all like that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15426346 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6165194\charrsid8142759 Do you remember your father doing anything for the children in the house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5185091 AL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6165194\charrsid8142759 He'd do anything you know, if mother wanted him to, you know, he was quite nice old chap, Suffolk. Lovely family in Suffolk.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15426346 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6165194\charrsid8142759 I remember you saying last week that your mother .. (Mrs. Lambert) in a bag or something, and 
we used to go to the shop and get a ha' p' orth of treacle and have it on our bread.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15426346 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6165194\charrsid8142759 And did she give you any other pocket money?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5185091 AL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6165194\charrsid8142759 No. Never had no pocket money, hadn't got money to give you. Look what children have to spend now. We ain't got it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15426346 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6165194\charrsid8142759 Did your mother and father belong to any clubs or go to any meetings?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5185091 AL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6165194\charrsid8142759 No. Used to pay in clubs like, er, benefit clubs and doctors club, you had to pay in the doctor's club, and that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15426346 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6165194\charrsid8142759 But social clubs, institutes .. ?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5185091 AL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6165194\charrsid8142759 There was nothing (..) of that on then (..) we had nothing.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15426346 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6165194\charrsid8142759 Could you tell me again, I was interested last week, but I didn't get it on this, about your Granny when you used to go to Brightlingsea.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5185091 AL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6165194\charrsid8142759 Oh, yes, used to walk over the marshes. She used to have a ba
sket on her arm, and I can't quite remember, that was, I think there was chickens, or, I don't know, things she used to (..) take to Brightlingsea with her. We walked over the marshes. She used to go found the shops and sell them, sell them. I forget what
 it was Granny had in her basket, but I think they was some chickens, and odds and ends and things, I don't know whether she had any eggs, I can't tell you, I forget now. It was a long while ago.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15426346 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6165194\charrsid8142759 When you were a child where did you eat your meals? What room did you eat them in?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5185091 AL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6165194\charrsid8142759 
Well, There wasn't much room to eat, was there, there was a kitchen where you had to do everything, and then there was the other room. We were generally in the front room.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15426346 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6165194\charrsid8142759 In those days, did you have anything different on Sundays?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5185091 AL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6165194\charrsid8142759 
Well, no, I can't tell you that we did you know, just used to have what mother'd got. Sometimes she used to make pies and things like that, puddings, but we had very plain living.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15426346 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6165194\charrsid8142759 I remember you saying you used to get a little joint. Could your mother not manage to do that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5185091 AL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6165194\charrsid8142759 (..) No, yes, a little joint was something we used to have. I tell you what my (..) used to have, half a (..) \{ILLEGIBLE\}
 head. That's very nice that was, sheep's head, things like that. We had (..) that was from the (..)
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15426346 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6165194\charrsid8142759 Did you have to do any gardening? When you were a child.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5185091 AL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6165194\charrsid8142759 
No, I didn't do much; we used to do a little, we didn't do much gardening. I was never very keen like, well, I didn't have much time. I went out to work.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15426346 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6165194\charrsid8142759 You told me your mother used to go out, gleaning. Did she ever have anybody come into the house to look after her girls?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5185091 AL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6165194\charrsid8142759 No. Well, my granny, her mother lived almost next door. She used to be there you see. Granny used to help her.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15426346 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6165194\charrsid8142759 Did you have any help from relatives and friends? They helped you when you were ill, didn't they, you told me?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5185091 AL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6165194\charrsid8142759 Oh, yes, yes, they did a bit, but, you know, we had to manage best we could.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15426346 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6165194\charrsid8142759 You were telling me, when you were going to get married. Your aunt and uncle knew about your young man, before your parents.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5185091 AL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6165194\charrsid8142759 Oh, yes, they did.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15426346 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6165194\charrsid8142759 What did your parents think when they found out?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5185091 AL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6165194\charrsid8142759 Oh, they sort of said, oh, I remember what mother said, oh, she said, well, you must bring him home with you one night.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15426346 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6165194\charrsid8142759 Did you have to save up money before you got married?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5185091 AL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6165194\charrsid8142759 
Oh, yes, I did save some, but my husband was very good; he he got enough saved to get a home (..) with .. I didn't used to have a lit you know.
\par 
